    "DEPARTMENT OF LIBRARIES V r jg\u00dfa\u00dfa\u00dfj V Yj H jttilW GEORGE B MORELAND r iHJL Department of Public Libraries provides modern aervicea to all residents of the county This is achieved by furnishing professional advice and reference services at its headquarters in Gaithersburg 12 branches and three bookmobiles and by loaning books periodicals pamphlets maps recordings and films for home use There were 2184289 books loaned for home use in 1959 an increase of 252024 over 1958 This represents bet ter than six books loaned per capita far above the na tional average compiled by the Department of Health Edu cation and Welfare George B Moreland is the Director of Public Libra ries Holder of two degrees in Library Science Moreland has attended Princeton University University of Pittsburgh and Carnegie Institute of Technology Moreland has served as a Supervisor with the D C Public Library System and as a librarian at the U S Mer chant Marine Academy in Johnstown Pa During World War II he was a lieutenant Senior grade in the Mari time Service He is a member of the American Library Association and is past president of the Maryland Library Association Moreland is married to the former"
